# piano2sheet — project rules

`piano2sheet` is a local GPU (CUDA) CLI: piano audio (YouTube link or local file) → engraved sheet
music (MusicXML + PDF). Flow: yt-dlp → ffmpeg (44.1 kHz mono) → Transkun (CUDA, audio→MIDI) →
hand-split (`src/notation.py`) → key/modulation detection (`src/keysig.py`) → MuseScore engrave
(`src/engrave_keys.py`). Full contract: `AGENTS.md`.

## Always
- **Title + composer are mandatory on every score.** Order: explicit `--title`/`--composer` → else
  auto-extract from the YouTube video metadata → else fail. Local-file input requires both. Pass them
  explicitly when the user names the song/artist; never hard-code a song's values in the code.
- Run inside the venv: `source .venv/bin/activate` then `python src/pipeline.py ...`.
- Keep artifacts under the per-job `runs/<name>/` folder.
- Wrap MuseScore invocations in `timeout` + retry (`_ms_run`); `xvfb-run` can hang.

## Never
- Never commit `cache/` (YouTube session cookies = secrets) or any token.
- Never commit `.venv/` or the large `runs/**/01_raw_audio.*` and `runs/**/02_audio_*.wav` intermediates.
- Never add narrating comments; comments explain non-obvious *why* only.

## Engraving facts (don't relearn the hard way)
- MuseScore ignores MIDI key/time-signature meta on import — apply per-section key signatures and a
  forced meter in music21 (`engrave_keys.py`), not via MIDI meta.
- Respell a modulated section by lowering it to the base key, letting MuseScore spell it, then
  transposing it back by a named interval.
- MusicXML `<scaling>` overrides the style `Spatium` (set staff size via `_set_scaling`).

## Style
Python, 4-space indent, ~100-col lines, `black`. Verify edits parse before finishing.
